---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Home" description="Your safe space for vibe coding. Security, automation, and publishing tools for AI-assisted developers.">

<section class="hero">
  <h1>Your safe space for vibe coding</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">
    You vibe, we watch your back. Security scanning, browser automation,
    multi-channel messaging, and instant publishing &mdash; all the tools
    a relaxed coder needs. Free and open source.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>What we make</h2>

  <div class="product">
    <h3>safe-space</h3>
    <p>
      Security guardrails for AI coding agents. Three layers of protection: a real-time
      hook guard that blocks dangerous commands before they execute, a log scanner that
      audits your sessions for vulnerabilities, and a cloud scanner for an external perspective.
      Catches prompt injection, credential exfiltration, and suspicious file access.
      You get a detailed report you can actually read.
    </p>
    <div class="product-actions">
      <div class="install-cmd" onclick="copyCmd(this)">npx safe-space scan</div>
      <a href="/p/safe-space-example">see example report</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/Chill-AI-Space/safe-space">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="product">
    <h3>active-listening</h3>
    <p>
      Aggregates incoming messages from Email, Telegram, WhatsApp, and LinkedIn
      into one stream. Your AI assistant reads the context, drafts a thoughtful response,
      and waits for your approval. You review, maybe tweak a word, hit send.
      Less context switching, more genuine connection.
      Everyone around you gets faster, warmer replies &mdash; and you barely lifted a finger.
    </p>
    <div class="product-actions">
      <div class="install-cmd" onclick="copyCmd(this)">npx active-listening init</div>
      <a href="https://github.com/Chill-AI-Space">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="product">
    <h3>multi-session-browser</h3>
    <p>
      Run multiple isolated browser sessions at once, each tied to a specific project
      and Google account. No more logging in and out. Works across machines too &mdash;
      your AI agent browses on one computer while you work undisturbed on another.
      Built on Playwright and Chrome DevTools Protocol.
    </p>
    <div class="product-actions">
      <div class="install-cmd" onclick="copyCmd(this)">npx multi-playwright setup</div>
      <a href="https://github.com/Chill-AI-Space/multi-playwright">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="product">
    <h3>behalf</h3>
    <p>
      A Chrome extension that extracts content from sites with heavy authentication
      and anti-scraping protection. When you are logged in, Behalf can reach pages
      that no parser or crawler ever could. Feed that data to your AI agent
      and actually get useful answers about real content behind login walls.
    </p>
    <div class="product-actions">
      <div class="install-cmd" onclick="copyCmd(this)">npx behalf install</div>
      <a href="https://github.com/Chill-AI-Space/behalf-chrome-extension">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="product">
    <h3>instant-publish</h3>
    <p>
      Turn any document into a shareable link &mdash; private by default.
      Your AI generates clean HTML, you deploy with one command, and every page
      gets a unique password automatically. No sign-ups, no accounts &mdash;
      just a link with <code>?password=</code> that you share with the right people.
      Way faster than wrestling with PDFs or Google Docs permissions.
    </p>
    <div class="product-actions">
      <div class="install-cmd" onclick="copyCmd(this)">npx instant-publish deploy ./my-doc.html --slug my-report</div>
      <a href="/p/death-to-pdf">see example report</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/Chill-AI-Space/instant-publish">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="product">
    <h3>auto-pilot</h3>
    <p>
      Keeps your Claude Code sessions running autonomously. Tracks session state
      across projects, coordinates handoffs between sessions, and delegates
      browser tasks to the right machine. When your AI agent finishes a step,
      auto-pilot moves to the next one &mdash; so you can go grab a coffee.
    </p>
    <div class="product-actions">
      <div class="install-cmd" onclick="copyCmd(this)">npx auto-pilot start</div>
      <a href="https://github.com/Chill-AI-Space/claude-auto-submit">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="product">
    <h3>second-desk</h3>
    <p class="product-tagline">Second desk for web browsing.</p>
    <p>
      Your AI agent needs a browser constantly &mdash; research, form filling, scraping,
      testing. That eats your RAM and steals your focus. Second-desk routes all browser
      tasks to another machine over the internet. Run <code>serve</code> on Machine B,
      get a pairing code, <code>connect</code> from Machine A. Your coding laptop stays
      fast and quiet. The second machine handles Chrome. Works with any machine: an old
      laptop, a Raspberry Pi, or a cloud VM.
    </p>
    <div class="product-actions">
      <div class="install-cmd" onclick="copyCmd(this)">npx second-desk serve</div>
      <a href="https://github.com/kobzevvv/second-desk">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr />

<section class="section">
  <h2>How it compares</h2>
  <table class="comparison-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Feature</th>
        <th>chillai.space</th>
        <th>Snyk</th>
        <th>SonarQube</th>
        <th>DIY scripts</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>AI agent security hooks</td>
        <td class="check">yes</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Prompt injection detection</td>
        <td class="check">yes</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Real-time command blocking</td>
        <td class="check">yes</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td>maybe</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Session log forensics</td>
        <td class="check">yes</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Multi-channel messaging</td>
        <td class="check">yes</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Browser automation</td>
        <td class="check">yes</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
        <td class="cross">no</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Free &amp; open source</td>
        <td class="check">yes</td>
        <td>freemium</td>
        <td>partial</td>
        <td class="check">yes</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Setup time</td>
        <td>2 min</td>
        <td>30 min</td>
        <td>1 hour+</td>
        <td>forever</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<hr />

<section class="section">
  <h2>Get started</h2>
  <p>
    Copy this prompt, paste it into your AI coding assistant,
    and let it handle the rest. It already knows your OS, your tools, your setup.
    Just tell it what you want.
  </p>

  <div class="prompt-box" id="setup-prompt">
    <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyPrompt()">copy</button>Hey, I just found chillai.space and I want to try their tools.
Check out https://github.com/Chill-AI-Space — they have
security scanning, browser automation, a Chrome extension
for scraping authenticated pages, and some other stuff.

Look at what I have on my machine and figure out which
tools make sense for me. Then install them. If something
needs config, set it up with sane defaults. Keep it chill.</div>
</section>

<script is:inline>
function copyPrompt() {
  const text = document.getElementById('setup-prompt').textContent
    .replace('copy', '').trim();
  navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
  const btn = document.querySelector('.copy-btn');
  btn.textContent = 'copied';
  setTimeout(() => btn.textContent = 'copy', 2000);
}

function copyCmd(el) {
  navigator.clipboard.writeText(el.textContent.trim());
  const original = el.textContent;
  el.textContent = 'copied!';
  el.classList.add('copied');
  setTimeout(() => {
    el.textContent = original;
    el.classList.remove('copied');
  }, 1500);
}
</script>

</Base>
